- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of feed-forward networks for parsing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper explores ways to reduce the size of features and embeddings without sacrificing accuracy. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for parsing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses reducing the size of embeddings, which is a common technique in computer vision tasks.
